Footnotes[edit]

  1. ^ Territory of Finland.
  2. ^ a b c d e f g h Also translated as commune.
  3. ^ a b c d e f g h i j k Territory of the United Kingdom.
  4. ^ Yerevan has no official term for its status as a first-level division.
  5. ^ Nassau is under direct control of the Bahamian government and is not part of any district.
  6. ^ a b Porto-Novo is the official capital and houses the National Assembly. However, the rest of the Beninese government, along with twenty-one embassies, are located in Cotonou.
  7. ^ a b Naypyidaw is the official capital since 2006 and houses the entire Myanma government. However, because this transfer was completely unknown until it had already occurred, forty-one embassies remain in the former capital, Yangon.
  8. ^ a b Also translated as municipality.
  9. ^ a b c Territory of the Netherlands.
  10. ^ De facto three separate entities.
  11. ^ a b Santiago is the official capital and houses most of the Chilean government and sixty-nine embassies. However, since 1990 the National Congress of Chile have been meeting in Valparaíso.
  12. ^ a b Malabo is the official and current capital and houses twenty-one embassies. However, the Equatorial Guinean government is currently in the process of transferring to the future capital, Oyala.
  13. ^ Usually translated as chartered city.
  14. ^ a b Territory of Denmark.
  15. ^ a b Berlin is the official capital since 1990 and houses most of the German government and 150 embassies. However, at least six federal government ministries and five embassies remain in the former West German capital, Bonn.
  16. ^ Also referred to as stadtstaat (city-state).
  17. ^ a b Territory of the United States.
  18. ^ Also referred to as municipality.
  19. ^ Yamoussoukro is the official capital since 1983. However, this status has been on paper only, as the entire Ivorian government, as well as forty-seven embassies, remain in the Ivory Coast's former capital, Abidjan.
  20. ^ Saint Helier is the official capital and houses most of the Jerseyan government. However, the official residence of the Lieutenant Governor is in nearby Saint Saviour.
  21. ^ Also translated as either region or oblast.
  22. ^ Also translated to as prefecture.
  23. ^ Also referred to as pilsēta (city).
  24. ^ Kuala Lumpur is the official capital and houses the Parliament of Malaysia, the official residence of the Yang di-Pertuan Agong, the Ministry of International Trade and Industry, and ninety-six embassies. However, the rest of the Malaysian government are located in Putrajaya.
  25. ^ a b c d e f Territory of France.
  26. ^ Seoul is the official capital and houses most of the South Korean government and 110 embassies. However, at least nine ministries have moved to what was supposed to be the future capital, Sejong.
  27. ^ Usually translated as urban municipality.
  28. ^ Usually translated as rural municipality.
  29. ^ Palikir is the official capital and houses the entire Micronesian government and one embassy. However, three embassies remain in the former capital, and current capital of the Pohnpei State, Kolonia.
  30. ^ Dhaka is one of four cities in Bangladesh that are not part of any subdistrict.
  31. ^ Sucre is the official capital since 2009 and houses the Supreme Tribunal of Justice. However, the rest of the Bolivian government, along with thirty-one embassies, remain in Bolivia's former capital, La Paz.
  32. ^ a b Also referred to as commune.
  33. ^ Jerusalem is the official capital and houses the entire Israeli government. However, because Israel's claim over Jerusalem is unrecognized, eighty-six embassies are instead located in Tel Aviv.
  34. ^ Yangon is spread out to include townships from North, South and East Yangon in addition to the entirety of West Yangon.
  35. ^ Belmopan is the official capital since 1970 and houses the entire Belizean government and seven embassies. However, six embassies remain in Belize's former capital, Belize City.
  36. ^ a b c Territory of Australia.
  37. ^ Non-UN member sovereign state. In free association with New Zealand.
  38. ^ a b Territory of China.
  39. ^ Non-UN member sovereign state. Has observer status.
  40. ^ Sections claimed by at least eight countries. De facto a condominium.
  41. ^ Territory of Norway.
